00:25:06.309 --> 00:25:08.225
that operate at sort of
subway-level headways.

00:25:08.225 --> 00:25:09.939
So it wouldn't be
included in your--

00:25:09.939 --> 00:25:11.980
PROFESSOR: So yeah, we're
not counting them here.

00:25:11.980 --> 00:25:15.750
And so good point,
it's hard to--

00:25:15.750 --> 00:25:18.960
there are many ways of
accounting for systems here.

00:25:18.960 --> 00:25:21.095
Sometimes, you know--

00:25:21.095 --> 00:25:23.119
AUDIENCE: Commuter
rail and heavy rail.

00:25:23.119 --> 00:25:24.660
PROFESSOR: Yeah,
that might be mixed.

00:25:24.660 --> 00:25:26.700
Or do they count
those as two or as one

00:25:26.700 --> 00:25:28.950
if there are different
systems in one city?

00:25:28.950 --> 00:25:32.340
I've tried here to count
each city as one system,

00:25:32.340 --> 00:25:34.150
even if there are
multiple systems.

00:25:34.150 --> 00:25:39.240
So for example, I'm not
counting the Tube in London

00:25:39.240 --> 00:25:41.880
and Docklands Light
Railway as two systems.

00:25:41.880 --> 00:25:43.184
I'm counting them as one.

00:25:43.184 --> 00:25:44.850
But some people would
count them as two.

00:25:44.850 --> 00:25:47.610
So there is some
arbitrary choice

00:25:47.610 --> 00:25:50.370
to be made here in
accounting, but it gives you

00:25:50.370 --> 00:25:52.860
an idea of what the trends
are and how we are moving

00:25:52.860 --> 00:25:55.670
and how it started and
where we are right now.

00:25:55.670 --> 00:25:58.932
Here's light rail, light
rail and streetcar.

00:25:58.932 --> 00:26:00.390
So if we only looked
at light rail,

00:26:00.390 --> 00:26:01.250
it wouldn't look like this.

00:26:01.250 --> 00:26:02.750
This includes
streetcars, and that's

00:26:02.750 --> 00:26:11.750
why we start so early before
the 1900s in Europe and Asia

00:26:11.750 --> 00:26:12.860
as well.

00:26:12.860 --> 00:26:15.860
And then North America really
didn't follow until much

00:26:15.860 --> 00:26:17.070
more recently.

00:26:17.070 --> 00:26:20.370
AUDIENCE: Well, North America,
it's like [INAUDIBLE]..

00:26:20.370 --> 00:26:23.027
If you include North America,
