00:47:35.330 --> 00:47:39.910
And if we divide that
by type, about 44%

00:47:39.910 --> 00:47:43.600
was spent in vehicle
operations, and the rest of it

00:47:43.600 --> 00:47:46.000
was more or less evenly
distributed between vehicle

00:47:46.000 --> 00:47:48.250
maintenance, other
kinds of maintenance

00:47:48.250 --> 00:47:51.970
like facility maintenance,
administration,

00:47:51.970 --> 00:47:53.900
and purchased transportation.

00:47:53.900 --> 00:47:57.760
Purchased transportation is
when a public agency outsources

00:47:57.760 --> 00:48:01.390
the operation of some mode.

00:48:01.390 --> 00:48:06.550
Most of this 14% is paratransit,
so on-demand transportation

00:48:06.550 --> 00:48:10.900
for the handicapped
and other groups.

00:48:10.900 --> 00:48:13.120
Some of it is commuter rail.

00:48:13.120 --> 00:48:17.740
So for example, the MBTA
operates commuter rail

00:48:17.740 --> 00:48:19.520
through a third party.

00:48:19.520 --> 00:48:25.530
All right, OK, by mode, about
half is spent on buses--

00:48:25.530 --> 00:48:28.530
makes sense because there are
more bus systems and, even

00:48:28.530 --> 00:48:31.140
in cities that have
rail, but the bus systems

00:48:31.140 --> 00:48:34.800
are quite large, and
they cover a wide area--

00:48:34.800 --> 00:48:38.030
about 20% on heavy
rail, 13% commuter rail,

00:48:38.030 --> 00:48:39.880
and much less on light rail.

00:48:39.880 --> 00:48:43.050
Paratransit is about
12%, 3% for other modes.

00:48:43.050 --> 00:48:46.302
Other modes is things like
ferries and other modes not

00:48:46.302 --> 00:48:48.510
included in the traditional
bus, heavy rail, commuter

00:48:48.510 --> 00:48:49.674
rail, light rail.

00:48:49.674 --> 00:48:58.050
So OK, and let's
look at vehicles--

00:48:58.050 --> 00:48:59.790
sorry, employees
per running vehicle.

00:48:59.790 --> 00:49:02.550
So by mode, how many
employees would you

00:49:02.550 --> 00:49:06.590
have to have to operate,
to run a system?

00:49:06.590 --> 00:49:09.600
So paratransit, about
1.6 per vehicle--

00:49:09.600 --> 00:49:12.210
obviously, you have one person
driving a paratransit vehicle.

00:49:12.210 --> 00:49:13.740
That person has an
eight-hour shift,

00:49:13.740 --> 00:49:15.690
and you run that vehicle
for a longer time.

00:49:15.690 --> 00:49:20.350
So you need more
people than vehicles.

00:49:20.350 --> 00:49:23.670
Bus tends to be higher
because bus systems tend

00:49:23.670 --> 00:49:27.600
